AC  GenProp0143
DE  Leloir pathway (galactose/glucose interconversion)
TP  PATHWAY
AU  Haft D
TH  0
DC  Galactose metabolism
DR  KEGG; map00052;
CC  The Leloir pathway can interconvert galactose and glucose, often for
CC  galactose degradation. It tends to be found in the Firmicutes. It
CC  includes galactokinase, galactose-1-P uridylyltransferase, and
CC  UDP-galactose 4-epimerase.
**  (was in groups table first).  This property has just (July 2005) been
**  revised by adding the mutarotase (Pfam subfamily version), with
**  TIGRFAMs version on the way, I hope. DHH.
